tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and low total COâ, suggesting possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, supporting renal dysfunction and possible tubular damage. HbA1c is low, excluding chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and further assessment of metabolic status.
